The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Wednesday, August 11, 2004 				 Colombo US embassy shut
																								Colombo, Aug. 10 (Reuters): The US embassy in Sri Lanka was evacuated and closed indefinitely today because of a security threat, an embassy spokesman said.																								He did not give details, but police said someone at the embassy received a letter containing white powder, raising fears of anthrax. It closed this afternoon due to an administrative and security incident, a spokesman said. 
